    <body>
        <h1><font size=6>Short Story:</font> 
            <font size=5 face="arial">
                <font color=red>A</font> 
                <font color=orange>Good</font> 
                <font color=yellow>Meal</font>
            </font></h1>


    <font face="arial" font size="4">
        <br>
        <p>The children were <font face=forte size="5">hungry</font>. They looked out the window. Where was their mother? She </p>
        <p>walked into the house. The children ran over to her. "Mama, we're so <font face=forte size="5">hungry</font>,"they both</p>
        <p>said.</p>
        <br>

        <br>
        <p>She said lunch was coming. She walked into the kitchen.She opened a can of chicken soup.</p>
        <p><u>She poured the soup into a pot</u>. She added water. She put the pot on the stove. She made</p>
        <p>two peanut butter and jelly sandwiches. She sliced an apple. The soup was <font face=forte size="5">hot</font>.</p>
        <br>

        <br>
        <p><strike>She poured it into two bowls </strike>. She put the sandwiches on two plates. She put apple slices on</p>
        <p>each plate. She put the bowls and plates on the table. The children ran to the table. <i>"Thank</p>
        <p>you, mommy!"</i> they said. Then they started eating. The cat and the dog watched them eat.</p>
        <br>
    </font>
